A fire on Monday morning broke out at the JKUAT main campus in Juja, Kiambu county, and badly damaged the students' dining hall. The inferno broke out at around 4 am. The fire razed several retail shops within the Hall 6 Cafeteria. Fire engines quickly responded and were able to contain the inferno. Efforts to get a comment from the school's administration were not successful as they declined to speak to the press. The source of the fire has not yet been confirmed. While confirming the incident, Juja OCPD Samuel Thirikwa said no casualty was reported in the morning inferno. Click here for the latest political news